## Detection Overview
Detects persistence via modification of an existing Linux user account to UID 0 using `usermod`.

## Log Source
- Linux process creation (auditd / Sysmon for Linux)

## Detection Logic
- Monitors `/usr/sbin/usermod`
- Requires `-u 0` argument using AND logic to reduce false positives

## False Positives
- Rare administrative recovery activity
- Should be reviewed outside change windows

## MITRE ATT&CK
- Persistence
- Account Manipulation (T1098)
